    "Id": "chassisdef_sirocco_SRC-2M",
    "Name": "Mammoth",
    "Details": "The Sirocco proved such an effective and stable weapons platform that Corean Enterprises decided to use it as a platform for testing captured and purchased Clan technologies. After some tense negotiations with several combat commands that fought against the Clans during the invasion, Corean managed to acquire a supply of Clantech Gauss Rifles and LRM-20 launchers which gave rise to the SRC-2M, nicknamed the Mammoth Mk. II (as it was the second testbed). Armed with two each of the Clantech weapons, as well as two Inner Sphere grade Machine Guns, the Mammoth proved powerful and dangerous and saw limited deployment with the FWLM, as well as the Word of Blake.\n\n\n <b><color=#e51717>COMMUNITY CONTENT</color></b>",
